ar qualities to the way the Sky Ryders operated\u2014they highlight and encourage the idea of everyone in the organization as family.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.drumcorpsplanet.com/forums/index.php/topic/144666-sky-ryders-alumni-scholarship-campaign/|title=Sky Ryders Alumni Scholarship Campaign|work=Drum Corps Planet Forums|accessdate=February 1, 2015}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.facebook.com/pages/Sky-Ryders-Alumni-Scholarship/180328795338474|title=Sky Ryders Alumni Scholarship|work=Facebook|accessdate=February 1, 2015}}</ref>\n\n==Notable alumni==\nFormer members of the Sky Ryders have gone on to make significant contributions within the [[Drum and bugle corps (modern)|Drum and Bugle Corps]] and [[Winter Guard]] activities. Some alumni have attained international recognition for their achievements outside the marching arts.\n\n*'''Wes Cartwright''': designer for [[Santa Clara Vanguard]]; costume designer for Dance Sophisticates; program designer for Broken Arrow HS; program coordinator for Hillgrove HS, Prosper HS; visual designer and instructor for Union HS; visual designer for L.D. Bell HS<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.hillgroveband.com/about-us/wes-cartwrigh/|title=Wes Cartwright|publisher=|accessdate=February 1, 2015}}</ref>\n*'''Tommy Keenum''': Nashville singer/songwriter; designer for The Band Hall; designer for [[The Cadets Drum and Bugle Corps|The Cadets]], [[Santa Clara Vanguard Drum and Bugle Corps|Santa Clara Vanguard]], [[Phantom Regiment Drum and Bugle Corps|Phantom Regiment]], [[Carolina Crown Drum and Bugle Corps|Carolina Crown]], [[Blue Knights Drum and Bugle Corps|Blue Knights]], and Sky Ryders; designer for Lassiter HS, Carmel HS, Center Grove HS, and Pride of Cincinnati Marching Bands; designer for Fort\u00e9, Aimachi, and Final Analysis Winter Guards; designer for [[Music City Mystique]]<ref>{{cite web|url=http://thebandhall.com/about-us/|title=About Us|publisher=|accessdate=February 1, 2015}}</ref>\n*'''Karl Lowe''': WGI Hall of Fame member 2003; designer for Odyssey and Fantasia Winter Guards; designer for [[Blue Devils Drum and Bugle Corps|Blue Devils]], [[Santa Clara Vanguard Drum and Bugle Corps|Santa Clara Vanguard]], Suncoast Sound, and [[The Magic Drum and Bugle Corps|Magic of Orlando]]<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.wgi.org/contents/Hall-of-Fame.html|title=Hall Of Fame - WGI|publisher=|accessdate=February 1, 2015}}</ref>\n*'''Roman Montoya''': director for Black Gold Winter Guard; choreographer for Waxahachie Color Guard and Winter Guard; movement instructor for [[Santa Clara Vanguard Drum and Bugle Corps|Santa Clara Vanguard]], [[Glassmen Drum and Bugle Corps|The Glassmen]], Sky Ryders, and [[Bluecoats Drum and Bugle Corps|Bluecoats]]; director of bands at Donna Shepard Intermediate School<ref>[http://www.blackgoldwinterguard.com/staff.html North Texas Performing Arts Association - Staff]</ref>\n*'''Alan Mueggenborg''': owner of FLASH Visual Media; drill designer for [[Glassmen Drum and Bugle Corps|The Glassmen]]; visual coordinator and designer for The Woodlands HS; visual designer for Owasso HS; executive director for Black Gold Youth Foundation; director and visual designer for Black Gold Drum and Bugle Corps; instructor and visual designer for Union HS; guard instructor for Catoosa HS; guard instructor for Oklahoma State University<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.dci.org/news/view.cfm?news_id=fe9e4606-4ca0-468f-b66f-de0c2e800259|title=DCI.org News: Giving back and participating: A Profile of Alan Mueggenborg, Glassmen drill designer|publisher=|accessdate=February 1, 2015}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://flashvisualmedia.com/#/alan-bio/|title=FLASH Visual Media - Home|publisher=|accessdate=February 1, 2015}}</ref>\n*'''Chad Sexton''': drummer for [[311 (band)|311]]; owner of Chad Sexton's Drum City; \"rhythmatic\" visual artist<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.311.com/2006/07/essential-features-chad-sextons-drum-city-la-places|title=Essential Features: Chad Sexton\u2019s Drum City (LA Places)|publisher=|accessdate=February 1, 2015}}</ref>\n*'''J.D. Shaw''': international horn soloist and recording artist; brass arranger/composer for [[Santa Clara Vanguard Drum and Bugle Corps|Santa Clara Vanguard]], [[Phantom Regiment Drum and Bugle Corps|Phantom Regiment]], [[Boston Crusaders Drum and Bugle Corps|Boston Crusaders]], and [[The Academy Drum and Bugle Corps|The Academy]]; former French hornist, arranger, and co-owner for Boston Brass; Associate Professor of Horn at the University of South Carolina<ref>[https://www.scvanguard.org/programs/vanguard/news/?uuid=3e0d7923-389f-496e-bfe3-9eefa051c435 Santa Clara Vanguard - J.D. Shaw Joins Vanguard Design Team] {{webarchive|url=https://archive.is/20141228161224/https://www.scvanguard.org/programs/vanguard/news/?uuid=3e0d7923-389f-496e-bfe3-9eefa051c435 |date=December 28, 2014 }}</ref>\n*'''John Simpson''': DCI Hall of Fame member 2014; brass instructor for Sky Ryders<ref name=\"dcifame\">{{cite web|url=http://www.dci.org/about/fame/members.cfm|title=Drum Corps International :: Marching Music's Major League\u2122|publisher=|accessdate=February 1, 2015}}</ref>\n*'''[[Jason Sutter]]''': drummer for [[Marilyn Manson]], [[Smash Mouth]], [[New York Dolls]], [[Soundgarden]], [[Audioslave]], [[Foreigner (band)|Foreigner]], and others\n*'''Steve Vickers''': DCI Hall of Fame member 2007; publisher of Drum Corps World magazine<ref name=\"dcifame\"/>\n\nThomas Stubbs, St Louis Symphony Percussionist since 1970.\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist|30em}}\n\n==External links==\n*{{Official website | http://skyryders.com/}}\n*[http://hutchpost68.org/ American Legion Lysle Rishel Post 68 website]\n*[http://www.dci.org/news/view.cfm?news_id=0861dde8-cd29-463b-88a3-72d68ef1d2b8 DCI Video: 1981 Sky Ryders]\n*[http://www.dci.org/news/view.cfm?news_id=4929ec85-4b85-4b93-81ed-cfdafbbbbe92 DCI Video: 1982 Sky Ryders]\n*[http://www.dci.org/news/view.cfm?news_id=511ed592-4e2a-4898-9092-14174bff5384 DCI Video: 1986 Sky Ryders]\n*[http:/