hich was the equivalent of one-fifteenth of the network bandwidth available from London to New York.{{citation needed|date=October 2019}}\n\nWGCZ Holding also own [[Bang Bros]], DDF Network, [[Penthouse (magazine)|Penthouse magazine]], [[Private Media Group]] and has a controlling interest in the productions gathered under the Legal Porno brand.<ref name =\"theblast\">{{cite web |title='BangBros' Owner Buys Penthouse Biz For $11.2 Million |url=https://theblast.com/bangbros-buys-penthouse-auction-millions/ |website=[[The Blast (website)|The Blast]] |accessdate=6 June 2018 |date=5 June 2018}}</ref><ref name=\"avn\">{{cite web |author=Mark Kernes |title=Penthouse Bankruptcy Auction Results in New Ownership |url=https://avn.com/business/articles/legal/after-yesterdays-bankruptcy-auction-penthouse-has-a-new-owner-779541.html |website=[[avn.com]] |accessdate=6 June 2018 |date=5 June 2018}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |author=Gustavo Turner |title=Private Media Group Acquired by XVideos Parent Company WGCZ |url=https://www.xbiz.com/news/249330/private-media-group-acquired-by-xvideos-parent-company-wgcz |website=[[XBIZ]] |accessdate=5 January 2020 |date=2 January 2020}}</ref>\n\n==History==\nXVideos serves as a pornographic media aggregator, a type of website which gives access to adult content in a similar manner as YouTube does for general content.<ref name=\"Pink2.0\">{{cite book |last=Tsika |first=Noah |date=October 3, 2016 |title=Pink 2.0: Encoding Queer on the Internet |url=https://books.google.com/?id=0uBKDQAAQBAJ&pg=PA61&dq=xvideos#v=onepage&q=xvideos |location=Bloomington, IN |publisher=Indiana University Press |pages=61\u201362 |isbn=978-0253023230 }}</ref><ref name=\"Economist\" /> Video clips from professional videos are mixed with amateur and other types of content.<ref name=\"Pink2.0\" /><ref name=\"Economist\" /> By 2012, XVideos was the largest porn website in the world, with over 100 billion page views per month.<ref name=\"XBIZ2\">{{cite web |title=Report: The Internet Really Is for Porn |date=April 4, 2012 |publisher=[[XBIZ]] |author=Yagielowicz, Stephen |url=https://www.xbiz.com/news/146703/report-the-internet-really-is-for-porn |accessdate=August 31, 2017}}</ref> [[Fabian Thylmann]], the owner of [[MindGeek]], attempted to purchase XVideos in 2012 in order to create a monopoly of pornographic tube sites. The French owner of XVideos turned down a reported offer of more than $120 million by saying, \"Sorry, I have to go and play ''[[Diablo II]]''.\"<ref name=\"Economist\">{{cite news |title=Naked capitalism |date=September 26, 2015 |newspaper=[[The Economist]] |url=https://www.economist.com/news/international/21666114-internet-blew-porn-industrys-business-model-apart-its-response-holds-lessons |accessdate=August 31, 2017}}</ref> In 2014, XVideos controversially attempted to force content providers to either pledge to renounce the right to delete videos from their accounts or to shut down their accounts immediately.<ref name=\"avn1\">{{cite magazine |title=XVideos.com Tube Site Accused of Strong-Arming Uploaders |date=August 13, 2014 |magazine=[[AVN (magazine)|AVN]] |url=https://avn.com/business/articles/technology/xvideos-com-tube-site-accused-of-strong-arming-uploaders-569826.html |accessdate=August 31, 2017}}</ref>\n\n== Web traffic and ranking ==\n{{As of|2018|12}}, XVideos has been counted as the 10th most popular website in the world by [[SimilarWeb]] in overall category and 1st in the adult category.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.similarweb.com/top-websites|title=Top Websites in the world \u2013 SimilarWeb Website Ranking|website=www.similarweb.com|language=en|access-date=2018-12-20}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.similarweb.com/top-websites/category/adult|title=Top Adult Websites in the world|website=www.similarweb.com|language=en|access-date=2018-12-20}}</ref>\n\n== Censorship ==\n{{See also|Internet censorship}}\n\n=== India ===\n{{Further|Internet censorship in India}}\nIn 2015, the company was targeted by the Indian government on a list of 857 'pornographic' websites, which also included non-pornographic websites such as [[CollegeHumor]].<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.firstpost.com/india/xvideos-com-subtle-brilliant-response-govts-pornban-2378200.html|title=Xvideos.com has the most subtle but brilliant response to govt's #Pornban|date=2015-08-04|work=Firstpost|access-date=2017-08-29|language=en-US}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.bgr.in/news/xvideos-college-humor-lash-out-at-indian-government-after-porn-ban/|title=Xvideos, College Humor lash out at Indian government after porn ban {{!}} Latest Tech News, Video & Photo Reviews at BGR India|last=Akolawala|first=Tasneem|work=BGR India|access-date=2017-08-29|language=en-US}}</ref>\nIn 2018, major internet service providers blocked access to XVideos and other porn sites.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.timesnownews.com/technology-science/article/reliance-jio-bans-adult-websites-in-india-after-dot-orders-to-block-827-adult-websites-report/304516|title=Reliance Jio blocks porn websites in India after DOT orders closure of 827 adult websites: Report {{!}} Tech News|last=Jaitly|first=Rohan|date=2018-10-26|website=TimesNowNews.com|language=|archive-url=|archive-date=|url-status=|access-date=2019-01-20}}</ref>\n\n=== Lebanon ===\nIn 2014, Lebanon's Minister of Telecommunications has ordered Internet service providers to block six pornographic websites<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://smex.org/lebanon-blocks-six-porn-sites-sparks-fears-of-further-censorship/|title=Lebanon Blocks Six Porn Sites, Sparks Fears of Further Censorship|date=2014-09-11|website=SMEX: Channeling Advocacy|language=en-US|access-date=2019-10-10}}</ref> including XVideos. Some internet providers did not oblige, while others like Mobi DSL did.\n\n=== Malaysia ===\nIn 2015, the Malaysian government banned XVideos for violating the [[Communications and Multimedia Act 1998]], which bans \"obscene content\" from being digitally distributed.<ref>{{Cite news|url=h